notes.note: Rep from Orangeville Nissan called, says the vehicle needs a new rac and pinion. Asked why, as we just paid out a claim for a used rac and pinion back at the beginning of September. Advisor spilled the beans and informed us that when the used rac and pinion was put it by the previous repair facility, they did not save the immobilizer and software information from the old rac and pinion to be programmed into the new rac and pinion. So they installed the rac and pinion and started having issues with it after. Vehicle locked customer out (cannot start), vehicle cannot be driven currently. Informed rep that customer will need to go back to previous repair facility and have them redo the repair to correct as they did not properly do the replacement in the first place. M.P.
